      "message": "We are including hvf.h, so we get linker errors:\n\nUndefined symbols for architecture x86_64:\n  \"_hvf_cpu_synchronize_post_init\", referenced from:\n      _cpu_synchronize_all_post_init in cpus.o\n  \"_hvf_cpu_synchronize_post_reset\", referenced from:\n      _cpu_synchronize_all_post_reset in cpus.o\n  \"_hvf_cpu_synchronize_state\", referenced from:\n      _cpu_synchronize_all_states in cpus.o\n  \"_hvf_enabled\", referenced from:\n      _cpu_synchronize_all_states in cpus.o\n      _cpu_synchronize_all_post_reset in cpus.o\n      _cpu_synchronize_all_post_init in cpus.o\n      _qemu_cpu_kick_thread in cpus.o\n      _qemu_mutex_lock_iothread in cpus.o\n      _qemu_init_vcpu in cpus.o\n      _qemu_hvf_cpu_thread_fn in cpus.o\n      ...\n  \"_hvf_init_vcpu\", referenced from:\n      _qemu_hvf_cpu_thread_fn in cpus.o\n  \"_hvf_vcpu_destroy\", referenced from:\n      _qemu_hvf_cpu_thread_fn in cpus.o\n  \"_hvf_vcpu_exec\", referenced from:\n      _qemu_hvf_cpu_thread_fn in cpus.o\nld: symbol(s) not found for architecture x86_64\n\nbecause:\n\n- We don\u0027t include the .c files defining the things in hvf.h\n- We don\u0027t link against hypervisor framework.\n\nShould these be guarded by CONFIG_XXX?",
